			<div class="content" id="post-content-1139894">
									

<p>I like this just as much as <a href="/scp-140">SCP-140</a>. I loved all the gloriously intriguing detail. There was a lot of information about the SCP, but none of it was superfluous. A couple of things were bugging me though:<br />
1. If it says &quot;Point of Divergence&quot; as part of its normal text, that's kinda lame. If it was written in by hand, by a fanatical and obsessive member of the Church of the True History&#8230; then that's great.<br />
2. And I'm going to have to argue for human intelligence on this one. Why do we need to use so much computer-assisted technology when we can just have a Class-D read the book and tell us what happens. We can tell her we want to write her biography and have her tell us about her life&#8230; Actually, that would make a kick-ass Foundation Tale&#8230;</p>
<p>Awesome first post.</p>

